The paper proposes a new approach for time series modeling using shapelets and graph embeddings. This involves designing a two-level timing factor to extract time-aware shapelets and constructing a shapelet evolution graph to capture how shapelets evolve over time. The paper also conducts experiments on various datasets to validate the effectiveness of the proposed approach. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these are the most relevant areas for time series modeling and shapelet-based approaches. The sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible as they relate to graph embeddings and the use of networks to model time series data.
